	<Title>
		Recipe: Fresh tomato crostini
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Fresh tomato crostini &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip" />
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Combine tomatoes, basil, oil, garlic and pepper in a medium bowl. Cover and let stand 30 minutes. Divide tomato mixture with any juices among the toast. Serve at room temperature.
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4 plum tomatoes, chopped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup minced fresh basil&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 teaspoons olive oil&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 clove garlic, minced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Freshly ground pepper&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 pound crusty Italian peasant bread, cut into 4 slices and toasted&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
